    "body": "Co-authored-by: Co-authored-by: Kevin Hwang <kljc8@outlook.com>\r\n\r\nAI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\nCloses #33666.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nnvim relies on file checksums to determine undo history. Consequently, when a file is modified by another tool, the checksum validation fails, causing the undo history to be cleared.\r\n\r\nThis functionality causes nvim's undo history to be constantly wiped when collaborating with other tools (such as IDEs or Agents), making the undo feature invalid.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n[nvim-fundo](https://github.com/kevinhwang91/nvim-fundo) is a popular solution that is mature and has a large user base. With the assistance of AI, I refactored it; since its original code focuses on providing abstractions, the refactoring results were excellent. \r\n\r\nThe results of this refactoring are summarized as follows:\r\n- Async support now depends directly on [async.nvim](https://github.com/lewis6991/async.nvim), which is being considered for merging into nvim core.\r\n- 12 internal classes reduced to 3\r\n- 1562 lines of Lua code to 451\r\n\r\nWith all its features. View the full summary [here](https://github.com/ofseed/nvim-fundo/tree/nvim-plugin).\r\n\r\nThis PR is complete, but since its dependency `vim.async` has not been fully merged into nvim, it cannot be merged at this time. However, the refactored version (https://github.com/ofseed/nvim-fundo/tree/nvim-plugin) is available for installation and use.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
